{"id": 25004, "date": "1987-02-08T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1987-02-08T19:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "https://estreetshuffle.com/?p=25004"}, "modified": "2026-06-08T15:08:04", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-08T22:08:04", "slug": "matr-bruce-springsteen-bob-dylan-and-tom-petty-the-heartbreakers-im-cryin", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/02/08/matr-bruce-springsteen-bob-dylan-and-tom-petty-the-heartbreakers-im-cryin/", "title": {"rendered": "I&#8217;m Cryin&#8217;"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Bruce Springsteen is no stranger to Eric Burdon and The Animals.</p>\n<p>Bruce&#8217;s intense covers of &#8220;It&#8217;s My Life&#8221; (performed a remarkable 88 times over a three-year span in the mid-1970s) are legendary, certainly ranking among Bruce&#8217;s all-time best covers.</p>\n<p>Bruce was covering The Animals long before that, though. As far back as 1965 The Castiles performed &#8220;We Gotta Get Out of This Place&#8221; at a local psychiatric hospital only four months after The Animals originally released the song.\u00a0In 1967 The Castiles covered &#8220;San Franciscan Nights&#8221; in concert before it was even a month old.</p>\n<p>Despite Bruce&#8217;s obvious fondness for The Animals, though, he&#8217;s never covered one of their greatest hits at one of his own shows.\u00a0&#8220;I&#8217;m Crying&#8221; was one of The Animals&#8217; first singles, peaking at #19 on the Billboard Hot 100 and #8 on the U.K. Singles charts when it was released in September 1964.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/g7NpD1kUBt8?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Fortunately, though, the late great Tom Petty picked up the slack. &#8220;I&#8217;m Crying&#8221; was a frequent fixture of his sets from 1989 all the way through 2006.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/wX7VtDv1WkY?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>And very early in that run of shows, the stars aligned: On March 1, 1990, Tom Petty &amp; The Heartbreakers played The Forum in Los Angeles, and both Bruce Springsteen and Bob Dylan were on-hand for the occasion.</p>\n<p>Tom brought Bruce and Bob on stage during the encores for two songs, the latter of which was &#8220;I&#8217;m Crying.&#8221; Judging from the clip below, Bruce was more than happy to oblige.</p>\n<div id=\"v-4Sw2cr76-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='426' src='https://videopress.com/embed/4Sw2cr76?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p>That remarkable performance was the only time Bruce has ever performed &#8220;I&#8217;m Crying&#8221; to date, but that&#8217;s not the only reason this recording is special.</p>\n<p>While Tom and Bruce had made joint appearances before as backing vocalists at all-star benefits, the recording above is the first and only time Bruce and Tom\u00a0 ever traded lead vocals on stage.</p>\n<p><strong>I&#8217;m Crying<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> March 1, 1990 (Inglewood, CA)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> March 1, 1990 (Inglewood, CA)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 February 3, 2021</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Bruce covered The Animals as far back as his Castiles days, but he saved one of their greatest hits for his first and only on-stage team-up with Tom Petty.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69741, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_feature_clip_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false}, "categories": [4, 3617, 5], "tags": [803, 3080, 3078, 3079], "class_list": ["post-25004", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-cover-me", "category-it-takes-two", "category-meeting-across-the-river", "tag-bob-dylan", "tag-im-crying", "tag-the-animals", "tag-tom-petty-and-the-heartbreakers"], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "jetpack_featured_media_